<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[805,1399,1023,1931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[807,946,1024,1044]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">RECOGNITION</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hermans" authorityYear="2021" box="[965,1151,1023,1044]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siederi">
<emphasis box="[965,1151,1023,1044]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Polystachya siederi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in having ascending pseudobulbs on a very short rhizome, large leaf-like scales towards the middle of the inflorescence, an unbranched inflorescence densely racemose towards the apex, hirsute rachis and floral bracts, medium-sized flowers with ovate lateral sepals forming a short rounded mentum at the base, a lip three-lobed in the apical half, and a farinose disk with an ovoid to globular callus in the centre. Amongst the 
<taxonomicName authority="Hook." authorityName="Hook." box="[961,1150,1298,1320]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[961,1070,1298,1319]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Polystachya</emphasis>
Hook.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker" box="[1169,1318,1298,1320]" firstAuthor="Hooker" journalOrPublisher="Exot. Fl." pageId="11" pageNumber="50" part="2" refId="ref10013" refString="Hooker, W. J. (1824). Polystachya luteola. Exot. Fl. 2: t. 103." title="Polystachya luteola" type="journal volume" year="1824">Hooker 1824</bibRefCitation>
: t.103) species occurring in Madagascar, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hermans" authorityYear="2021" box="[1189,1280,1328,1350]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siederi">
<emphasis box="[1189,1280,1328,1350]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. siederi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has some vegetative and floral similarities to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridl." box="[1230,1399,1359,1381]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anceps">
<emphasis box="[1230,1330,1360,1381]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. anceps</emphasis>
Ridl.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley" box="[812,1011,1389,1412]" firstAuthor="Ridley" journalOrPublisher="J. Linn. Soc., Bot." page="473" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="456 - 523" part="21" refId="ref10932" refString="____ (1885). The Orchids of Madagascar. J. Linn. Soc., Bot. 21: 456 - 523." title="The Orchids of Madagascar" type="journal article" year="1885">Ridley 1885: 473</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Schltr." box="[1038,1259,1389,1411]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heckeliana">
<emphasis box="[1038,1173,1389,1411]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. heckeliana</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schlechter" firstAuthor="Schlechter" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Mus. Colon. Marseille" page="167" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="148 - 202" part="3" refId="ref11067" refString="____ (1913). Orchidacees de Madagascar. Orchidaceae Perrieranae Madagascarienses. Ann. Mus. Colon. Marseille, ser. 3. 148 - 202." title="Orchidacees de Madagascar. Orchidaceae Perrieranae Madagascarienses" type="journal article" year="1913">Schlechter 1913: 167</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schltr." box="[983,1195,1420,1442]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhodochila">
<emphasis box="[983,1115,1420,1442]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. rhodochila</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schlechter" firstAuthor="Schlechter" journalOrPublisher="Beih. Bot. Centralbl." page="323" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 341" part="34" refId="ref11158" refString="____ (1916). Orchidaceae Perrierianae (Collectio secunda), Beih. Bot. Centralbl. 34: 1 - 341." title="Orchidaceae Perrierianae (Collectio secunda)" type="journal article" year="1916">Schlechter 1916: 323</bibRefCitation>
) but it differs in having an unbranched inflorescence, slightly smaller flowers, and more oval lateral sepals and lip shape; it also has much shorter floral bracts than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schltr. (Schlechter" authorityYear="1916" box="[944,1077,1542,1564]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhodochila">
<emphasis box="[944,1077,1542,1564]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. rhodochila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In flower shape it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schltr. (Schlechter" authorityYear="1913" box="[928,1062,1573,1594]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heckeliana">
<emphasis box="[928,1062,1573,1594]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. heckeliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the lip is lobed in the apical half (vs the basal half), the callus is more distinct and the flower colour is also different. It shares a number of characteristics with several 
<taxonomicName box="[805,914,1695,1716]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[805,914,1695,1716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Polystachya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from mainland Africa: the inflorescence, lip shape and callus are most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schltr." box="[805,1069,1756,1778]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="transvaalensis">
<emphasis box="[805,980,1756,1778]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. transvaalensis</emphasis>
Schltr.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schlechter" box="[1094,1332,1756,1778]" firstAuthor="Schlechter" journalOrPublisher="Beibl. Bot. Jahrb. Syst." page="28" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="20 - 44" part="20" refId="ref11030" refString="Schlechter, R. (1895). Aufzahlung der von mir auf meiner letzten Reise durch Natal und Transvaal gesammelten Orchideen. Beibl. Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 20: 20 - 44." title="Aufzahlung der von mir auf meiner letzten Reise durch Natal und Transvaal gesammelten Orchideen" type="journal article" year="1895">Schlechter 1895: 28</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ridl." box="[805,988,1787,1809]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Polystachya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="albescens">
<emphasis box="[805,924,1787,1808]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">P. albescens</emphasis>
Ridl.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ridley" box="[1008,1203,1787,1809]" firstAuthor="Ridley" journalOrPublisher="Bol. Soc. Brot." page="199" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="196 - 216" part="5" refId="ref11003" refString="____ (1887). Catalogo da Flora da Ilha de S. Thome. Bol. Soc. Brot. 5: 196 - 216." title="Catalogo da Flora da Ilha de S. Thome" type="journal article" year="1887">Ridley 1887: 199</bibRefCitation>
) and its variants but it is distinct from both by its shorter and broader pseudobulbs, unbranched inflorescence, and slightly smaller flowers with shorter and more rounded ovate lateral sepals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
